Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
flipOrRotateObject(25.10)                            flipOrRotateObject(25.10)

Name
       flipOrRotateObject - Flips or rotates the selected objects

Syntax
        flipOrRotateObject

       [-help]

       [-keepRelative]

       {-flip {MX | MY} | -rotate {R90 | R180 | R270}}

       [-group]

       [-name <object>]

       Flips  or  rotates the selected objects. Alternatively, you can use the
       "Flip/Rotate Selected Objects" form in the Innovus GUI, to flip or  ro-
       tate an instance. Use this command after importing the design.

Parameters
       -flip {MX | MY}
              Flips the selected object(s) through x axis or y axis.

              Example: flipOrRotateObject -flip MX

              Before:

              After:

              Data_type: string, required

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each flipOrRotateObject  parameter.  For  a  de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man flipOrRotateObject

       -group Flips  or  rotates  the  bounding box which encloses all the se-
              lected objects.

              Example: flipOrRotateObject -flip MX -group

              Before:

              After:

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -keepRelative
              Calls the create_relative_floorplan command.  With  this  option
              enabled,  when  the anchor objects are rotated, the relative ob-
              jects are rotated and updated automatically.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -name <object>
              Specifies the name of the object you want to flip or rotate.

              Note: The objects can be modules,  groups,  placement  blockage,
              routing  blockage, hard Macros, special routings, special wires,
              and special vias (including 45 degree).

              Data_type: string, required

       -rotate {R90|R180|R270}
              Rotates the selected object(s) by 90 or 180 or 270 degrees.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command flips the selected object(s) through the x axis:

       flipOrRotateObject -flip MX

Related Information
              * flipchip_allow_routed_bump_edit

              * create_relative_floorplan

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

